TASK 4: NETWORK INTRUSION DETECTION SYSTEM
Title: Implementation of a Network Intrusion Detection System Using Snort
Introduction
A Network Intrusion Detection System (NIDS) monitors network traffic to identify suspicious activities and potential attacks.
Tools commonly used:
* Snort
* Suricata
Step 1: Installation
Install Snort:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install snort
Verify installation:
snort -V
Configure network settings:
sudo nano /etc/snort/snort.conf
Example:
ipvar HOME_NET 192.168.1.0/24
Step 2: Configure Rules and Alerts
Create a custom rule:
alert icmp any any -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"Ping detected"; sid:1000001; rev:1;)
Save:
/etc/snort/rules/local.rules
Restart:
```bash
sudo systemctl restart snort
```
## Step 3: Monitor Network Traffic
Run Snort:
sudo snort -A console -q -c /etc/snort/snort.conf -i eth0
The system continuously monitors traffic and displays alerts.
Step 4: Response Mechanisms
Responses include:
* Alert notifications
* Logging incidents
* Blocking suspicious IPs
Example:
sudo iptables -A INPUT -s 192.168.1.100 -j DROP
Step 5: Visualization Dashboard
Tools:
* Kibana
* Grafana
Dashboard features:
* Attack trends
* Alert graphs
* Traffic monitoring
* Threat statistics
Conclusion
The NIDS detects network threats early and improves overall system security.
